question: List track name, album title, and artist name for tracks with track id <= 15.
generated_sql:
SELECT T3.Name AS TrackName, T2.Title AS AlbumTitle, T4.Name AS ArtistName 
FROM PlaylistTrack AS T1 
INNER JOIN Track AS T3 ON T1.TrackId = T3.TrackId 
INNER JOIN Album AS T2 ON T3.AlbumId = T2.AlbumId 
INNER JOIN Artist AS T4 ON T2.ArtistId = T4.ArtistId 
WHERE T3.TrackId <= 15;

question: Show top 10 artists by quantity sold using InvoiceLine -> Track -> Album -> Artist.
generated_sql:
SELECT a.ArtistId, a.Name, SUM(il.Quantity) AS total_sold
FROM InvoiceLine il
JOIN Track t ON il.TrackId = t.TrackId
JOIN Album al ON t.AlbumId = al.AlbumId
JOIN Artist a ON al.ArtistId = a.ArtistId
GROUP BY a.ArtistId, a.Name
ORDER BY total_sold DESC
LIMIT 10;

question: Show top 10 customers by spending with their support rep names using Customer -> Invoice and Customer -> Employee.
generated_sql:
SELECT c.CustomerId, c.FirstName, c.LastName, e.FirstName AS SupportRepFirstName, e.LastName AS SupportRepLastName, SUM(i.Total) AS TotalSpent 
FROM Customer c 
JOIN Invoice i ON c.CustomerId = i.CustomerId 
JOIN Employee e ON c.SupportRepId = e.EmployeeId 
GROUP BY c.CustomerId, c.FirstName, c.LastName, e.FirstName, e.LastName 
ORDER BY TotalSpent DESC 
LIMIT 10

question: Show top 15 tracks by revenue contribution (quantity * unit price) with album and artist names.
generated_sql:
SELECT 
    T.Name, 
    A.Title AS AlbumTitle, 
    Ar.Name AS ArtistName, 
    SUM(T.UnitPrice * IL.Quantity) AS TotalRevenue
FROM 
    Track T
JOIN 
    InvoiceLine IL ON T.TrackId = IL.TrackId
JOIN 
    Invoice I ON IL.InvoiceId = I.InvoiceId
JOIN 
    Album A ON T.AlbumId = A.AlbumId
JOIN 
    Artist Ar ON A.ArtistId = Ar.ArtistId
GROUP BY 
    T.Name, 
    A.Title, 
    Ar.Name
ORDER BY 
    TotalRevenue DESC
LIMIT 15;

question: Give me invoices issued in 2012 and their bill nation, amount, and purchaser email.
generated_sql:
SELECT i.InvoiceId, c.Email, i.BillingCountry, SUM(il.UnitPrice * il.Quantity) AS TotalAmount
FROM InvoiceLine il
JOIN Invoice i ON il.InvoiceId = i.InvoiceId
JOIN Customer c ON i.CustomerId = c.CustomerId
WHERE strftime('%Y', i.InvoiceDate) = '2012'
GROUP BY i.InvoiceId, c.Email, i.BillingCountry;

question: Show each customer's age and favorite genre.
notes: Chinook Customer table has no age/favorite genre columns.
generated_sql:
SELECT c.CustomerId, c.FirstName, c.LastName, julianday('now') - julianday(c.BirthDate) AS Age, g.Name AS FavoriteGenre
FROM Customer c
JOIN Invoice i ON c.CustomerId = i.CustomerId
JOIN InvoiceLine il ON i.InvoiceId = il.InvoiceId
JOIN Track t ON il.TrackId = t.TrackId
JOIN Genre g ON t.GenreId = g.GenreId
WHERE g.Name = (
    SELECT g.Name
    FROM Genre g
    JOIN Track t ON g.GenreId = t.GenreId
    WHERE t.AlbumId IN (
        SELECT a.AlbumId
        FROM Album a
        JOIN Customer c2 ON a.ArtistId = c2.ArtistId
        WHERE c2.CustomerId = c.CustomerId
    )
    GROUP BY g.Name
    ORDER BY COUNT(*) DESC
    LIMIT 1
)

question: List suppliers and the products they supply.
notes: No Supplier/Product tables in Chinook core schema.
generated_sql: SELECT T2.Name AS SupplierName, T1.Name AS ProductName FROM Product AS T1 INNER JOIN Supplier AS T2 ON T1.SupplierId = T2.SupplierId

question: Show invoice payment method for each invoice.
notes: Invoice has no payment method column in this DB.
generated_sql:
SELECT i.InvoiceId, c.FirstName || ' ' || c.LastName AS CustomerName, il.UnitPrice * il.Quantity AS PaymentMethod
FROM InvoiceLine il
JOIN Invoice i ON il.InvoiceId = i.InvoiceId
JOIN Customer c ON i.CustomerId = c.CustomerId;
